733.description: I added the 5 phases for running, these are the pushoff phase, swing phase, early, mid and late stance phase (http://www.fit4duty.co.uk/strength-training/strength-training-for-runners). 4. Phase: mid stance phase

734.title: Running late stance phase
734.description: I added the 5 phases for running, these are the pushoff phase, swing phase, early, mid and late stance phase (http://www.fit4duty.co.uk/strength-training/strength-training-for-runners). 5. Phase: late stance phase

736.title: masculinize body
736.description:
When applied to the 50% everything default morph, this target masculinizes the body, and as requested by a user, reverts the head back to its original base.obj form. 

This target probably still has some bugs that need to get ironed out.  I'm also open to suggestions for what to name my targets.

738.title: teeth forward
738.description: Quick useful target that I've been meaning to do.

739.title: teeth lower
739.description: Goes well with my "teeth forward" target.

740.title: Female Top 01 white blue pattern
740.description: Playing around with a tileable texture released by Pixar (http://www.makehumancommunity.org/forum/viewtopic.php?f=8&t=14062). License is CC-BY 4.0 because it's required by Pixar.

741.title: Female Panties 01 white blue pattern
741.description: Playing around with a tileable texture released by Pixar (http://www.makehumancommunity.org/forum/viewtopic.php?f=8&t=14062). License is CC-BY 4.0 because it's required by Pixar.

742.title: eyes closed
742.description: simple easy pose for testing purposes

743.title: Uniform skin texture
743.description: This skin is uniform, with no body-part coloration or shading, similar to the default but with a somewhat realistic color and texture. It is useful for viewing the topology of the model without "drawn on" features but without the smooth-plastic appearance of the default material.  It could also be used as a base which can be altered to a desired skin color and on which body part coloration or textures are added.

745.title: Knitted Hat 01
745.description:
Tags: Hats.
Hand knitted hat.
In Blender use the "solidify" modifier with "Thickness" about 6mm and "Fill Rim" and "Only Rim" to give it some thickness.

Preview image rendered in Blender Cycles.

746.title: M Trousers 01
746.description:
Tags: Male, Trousers, Jeans, Pants.
Loose fit slightly dirty jeans for male makehuman character. Some texture and mesh distortion may occur between the legs in some poses.

They are ment to be used with at least one level subsurf.
In Blender use the "solidify" modifier with "Thickness" about 3mm and "Fill Rim" and "Only Rim" to give the fabric some thickness.

Preview image rendered in Blender Cycles and with subsurf level 2.

747.title: tennis dress
747.description: A typical tennis dress for female characters. It should be combined with sport briefs01 (for your own security ... :) ). A litsphere is used to make the normal map visible. Delete-groups are used.

748.title: tennis shoes
748.description: These shoes are derived from my running shoes. I combined the shoes with socks. Delete groups are used. A litsphere is used to make the normal map visible in Makehuman.

749.title: sport briefs 01
749.description: Since it is weird to wear fine lingerie under e.g. a tennis dress, I created sport briefs for female characters. Edit: A normal map is added, in MakeHuman I use the leather litsphere to make it visible. Delete groups are used. A sport bra is also available. If you want to use these briefs without an additional dress, you should use the red pole-dance material.

750.title: tennis racket
750.description: I created a tennis racket to complete the scene. You can download a few tennis poses, then you will see if it fits. In Blender you may change the frame of the racket to a more glossy material if you want ...

751.title: Tennis forehand volley
751.description: A typical tennis pose to be used with the tennis assets.

752.title: Tennis two-handed backhand
752.description: A typical tennis pose to be used with the tennis assets.

753.title: Tennis serve (wind-up)
753.description: A typical tennis pose to be used with the tennis assets.

754.title: nose cartilage
754.description: Meant to be used with jwc's skeleton clothing.

756.title: overheadblock
756.description: climbing stairs blocking overhead with shield

757.title: Female generic with simplified genitals
757.description:
This is derivative work of the female generic topology from the official distribution. Simplified genitals are similar to http://www.makehumancommunity.org/proxy/female_muscular_with_simplified_genitals.html.
Update 02/18/2019: Weight issue fixed.

767.title: xray
767.description: Spooky see through skin. Pictured here with jwc's skeleton.

768.title: Jammers Swimsuit 3
768.description: A men's "jammers" style swimsuit in black.

776.title: Jammers skin
776.description: A skin that paints jammers directly onto the body mesh.  It was created with Inkscape and could be used with any underlying skin.  This is mostly a demo.

777.title: Swinging_01
777.description:
Young girl swinging in the garden.

Thanks for Punkduck for basic training and Duarteemerich for nice swimsuit  :)

778.title: Sit_01A
778.description: Young lady sitting modest and elegant in armchair.

779.title: David
779.description: A crude approximation of the pose of Michelangelo's David, just intended as a naturalistic pose.

780.title: Retro polka dot skirt
780.description: This is a typical 50s skirt with a polka dot pattern. It should be combined with the appropriate retro top. Normal map is added, but most of the pleats are directly created by geometry. The pattern should work with subdivision in Blender, MakeHuman will distort it a bit. The normal map is made visible by using the leather litsphere. In Blender the litsphere does not matter.

781.title: Retro top
781.description: This is a typical 50s top. In reality it is convertible from a square neckline to a off shoulder neckline. It should be combined with the retro polka dot skirt. Normal map is added to create the pleats of the sleeves. The normal map is made visible by using the leather litsphere. In Blender the litsphere does not matter. Delete groups are used.

782.title: Abdominal Column
782.description: This is a crude attempt at modeling the fact that the abs (rectus abdominis) are actually a layer that sits on top of the lower external obliques (see top inset in illustration) which are quite flat, the abs thus form a column that protrudes from the torso.

783.title: Maria Top
783.description: Top for Maria Robotnik. Based off of PunkDuck's Retro Top.

784.title: Maria Skirt
784.description: Skirt for Maria Robotnik. Based off of PunkDuck's Retro polka dot skirt.

785.title: Maria Shoes
785.description: Shoes for Maria Robotnik. Based off of PunkDuck's comfortable sneakers.

788.title: Muay thai ankle support
788.description: This is the first clothing asset I have created using makeclothes. I made ankle support of the kind that is used in combat sports such as muay thai and MMA.

789.title: fix male nipple
789.description: The default male nipple is distorted in two ways, the end of the nipple is stretched out into a very oblong elipse instead of being circular, and the base of the nipple is a much larger radius than the end.  This target corrects the geometry, giving the nipple a basically cylindrical shape. However, the change in the base means the area covered by the base is significantly shrunk causing the surrounding area to be stretched.

790.title: F Trousers 01
790.description:
Tags: Female, Trousers, Jeans, Pants.
Jeans with embroidery for female makehuman character. There is already great female jeans made by punkduck but as I made this for a future scene I thought they may be useful for somebody else.

This time I did the whole belt area as tre vertex hard body to minimize deformation of the belt and buckle thereof fitness adjustments around that area may be necessary when posing.

Some texture and mesh distortion may occur between the legs in some poses.

In Blender use the "solidify" modifier with "Thickness" about 3mm and "Fill Rim" and "Only Rim" to give the fabric some thickness.

Preview image rendered in Blender Cycles with "tennis shoes" by punkduck and the top "floral" by o4saken.

791.title: off-shoulder long-sleeve top
791.description: This is a rather interesting piece of cloth. It is 10% transparent, so no delete-groups are used. The shirt is designed to fit to the tight jeans and the strapless bra. You may change the small rings to a shiny material in Blender. In Makehuman, the leather litsphere is used to make the normal-map visible.

792.title: lace-choker
792.description: A choker is a close-fitting necklace worn around the neck. I tried a simple lace-version with connecting rings at the backside. You should change these rings to a shiny material in Blender.

793.title: fez
793.description: the point of this was just to make a test clothing on a mesh with a target applied to it, but I'm uploading anyway

794.title: bodyparts3d skin
794.description: Caucasian male, shrinkwrapped to the 3.0 human skin from BodyParts3d.  CC-BY because the terms of the bodyparts3d license says to distribute it under the same license. I'm not sure if it even counts if you're not modifying/redistrubuting the actual obj though.  But it's still a cool site worth visiting.

795.title: cornea
795.description:
Just the cornea from the high poly eyes, as a separate object. 
Edit: punkduck was kind enough to make an improved material with texture, so I've uploaded it here. The texture is 1024x1024, because that's the minimum file size you can upload, but it's just a transparent square, so you can resize it to be smaller after downloading it. The screenshot has eyes set to "none", just to show the cornea.

796.title: eyes without cornea
796.description: The high poly eyes but with the cornea removed.

797.title: eyes real pupil (no cornea)
797.description: Eyes with an actual hole for the pupil.  This one has no cornea, it's a separate download. (When I put the cornea back on, it broke one of the faces on the eyeball and I have no idea why. )  The diffuse texture is just one of the default MH eye textures.  It works with all the same textures as the regular high poly eyes.

800.title: alpha7 head topology
800.description: The "auto ethnic skin" works beautifully in the material editor, but unfortunately right now the mhmat doesn't work even when you move it to the local folder (on windows, at least).  The current skin textures don't work either right now.  (Also, a weird dimple appears below the eyes when you change race to asian. )

801.title: harvey_proxy1
801.description:
updated v2.  fixed back of head. better conforms to mh default in midsection. fixed a couple rogue verts.  still has vert group issues stretches funny with extreme poses.  i edit skins after makehuman so i probably wont keep trying to fix this unless some one knows tricks to blend vert weights.  if you do please let me know. 
 
this is Adult Female Genitalia (old) uploaded by wolgade with some improvements.  increased mesh density in "important" areas fixed awkward inner thigh.  there is a couple rogue verts that fix with smoothing will probably update with v2 in future

802.title: harvey_midtoned_female
802.description:
this is a test medium toned female skin works well with harvey_proxy1
bastardized MH young african female skin with some added detail

803.title: halterneck romper
803.description: From Wikipedia:  "while rompers had been popular in among women in the 1950s, they re-emerged in the 1970s as a fashion for adult women. In the 1970s rompers were usually a casual garment made of terrycloth, and often in a tube top style. They were common in the 1980s in a wider variety of materials. Since 2006, rompers have enjoyed a minor renaissance as a fashionable garment for women." I made a romper with a halterneck. A normalmap is supplied and delete groups are used. Nevertheless it could happen that skin peeks through. Best fit on female characters with small to midsize breasts.

804.title: Fully close mouth
804.description: By default the lips are just slightly parted, this target closes them completely so that the teeth or inside of the mouth are not exposed.  A higher setting is required for female characters than for male characters.

805.title: baby-romper
805.description: After doing a romper for female adults here is one for our youngest MakeHuman characters. Delete groups and special groups for arms and body are used to allow posing of the arms. For the visibility of the normal map I used the leather litsphere.

806.title: Evening gown
806.description: This evening gown should be used for female characters. Because of the length of the gown there maybe problems for a lot of poses. Especially crossing the legs is not possible. Delete groups are only used in the upper section. In Blender change zipper and decoration in the neck region to another material (glass-like) or use node setup like similar to the image saved as bump texture. Subdivision surface algorithm in Blender or Makehuman will change the form of the decoration, this is intended. The leather litsphere is used in Makehuman to make the normalmap visible. Edit: changed because of problems with Asian characters and specular map added.

807.title: Bootcut Jeans
807.description: This is a bootcut Jeans for men.

808.title: Example/Test of Blender Particles Hair
808.description: Just an illustration of Blender particles hair converted to a mesh and run through MakeClothes.

809.title: Dagger
809.description: A little dagger i made sculpting in blender, fitted as a strap around the thigh on the average female . use with a nice split skirt or fancy lingerie.

810.title: deathnote t-shirt
810.description: This T-Shirt featuring the japanese manga series 'death note' is made by o4saken. My only work are a few fixes, I added a delete group and I upload everything so it should work with MakeHuman directly. The shirt was originally build for a male character but also works for females. Maybe you also have to fix a few vertices in Blender when you combine it with pants. For females it should work with the tight jeans. Please mention o4saken as the real author. The litsphere is used to make the normal map visible. I added diffuse map and normal-map but not the spec-map (because it consists of a pattern which is not identical with the cloth itself). For the example picture it was sufficient to connect diffuse-map and glossy shader ... (Thanx a lot for this work, o4saken!)

811.title: anatomically realistic skull
811.description:
This skull is pretty high poly; blender tells me it has 31,000 tris, so be warned.  And it doesn't use rigid groups, so there's no guarantee that it won't behave strangely when morphing. Which you won't see unless you use my xray skin, since it doesn't use delete groups. It's pretty basic, but still fun.  
Usually my stuff is CC0, but I'm setting it to CC-BY because the original obj was from bodyparts3d. I just converted it to quads. 
Resources used: 
Instant Meshes/MeshLab: https://github.com/wjakob/instant-meshes
BodyParts3d: http://lifesciencedb.jp/bp3d/

812.title: mouth scale increase (fixed)
812.description: I noticed that the mouth vertical scale increase target also affects the nose. This is my corrected version.

813.title: mouth trans down (fixed)
813.description: A corrected version of the mouth translate down target that doesn't change the nose.

814.title: mouth trans up (fixed)
814.description: A corrected version of the mouth translate up target that doesn't change the nose. The difference is pretty subtle compared to the mouth translate down version, but I'm uploading it for completeness' sake.

815.title: alpha 7 ear topology
815.description: A work in progress. Uses the alpha7 topology for the ear, grafted onto the current topology. Now your characters can properly wear earbuds!

816.title: female strapless bodysuit
816.description: This rather simple strapless bodysuit should be used for female characters. Normally it is used as a shape-wear, but you can use it for different purposes (e.g. as part of a costume). It is designed to fit with the ballet tights. Delete groups are used and a normal map is added and made visible in makehuman using the leather litsphere.

817.title: female knee boots
817.description: I created a pair of knee boots for female characters. The high heels section is simply created by deleting the whole feet + part of the leg using the delete-group. The boots could also be used with the ballet tights or the tight jeans. A normal map is added. You may change the material of the zipper to a metal shader in Blender.

818.title: evening gloves
818.description: Evening gloves or opera gloves are part of a formal outfit. But you can use these gloves also as part of a costume. Delete groups are used to delete hands and part of the arm. A normal map is added and made be visible in MakeHuman using the leather litsphere. The example picture combines the gloves with the evening gown (using an add-color node to make the blue gown white) in Blender. When you use the original white color for the gloves in Blender, reduce the strength of the normals to 0.5.

819.title: p-ivy decoration
819.description: Blender generated ivy decoration for a Poison Ivy cosplay character. It should be used with ballet tights and female knee boots. In Blender use subdivision surface modifier and put the color output of the diffuse texture into the displacement entry.

820.title: p-ivy weapon
820.description: A weapon created by O4saken. I got the permission to upload this weapon into the user contributions to allow users to create a complete Poison Ivy cosplay character. Normalmaps are added and made visible by the leather litsphere in Makehuman. All credits goes to O4saken ... thank you!

821.title: p-ivy bodysuit material
821.description: A material you should use for the Poison-Ivy cosplay character on the female strapless bodysuit. For the other assets see illustration.

822.title: p-ivy tights material
822.description: A material you should use for the Poison-Ivy cosplay character on the ballet tights. For the other assets see illustration.

823.title: p-ivy gloves material
823.description: A material you should use for the Poison-Ivy cosplay character on the evening gloves. For the other assets see illustration.

824.title: p-ivy boots material
824.description: A material you should use for the Poison-Ivy cosplay character on the female knee boots. For the other assets see illustration.

825.title: Hairstyle Curly 2 (red)
825.description: A material you should use for the Poison-Ivy cosplay character on the hairstyle Curly 2. It now uses an own diffuse texture, otherwise it will not work properly in Blender. I added the illustration for the cosplay character to show the hair color ... this material is just added for completeness.

826.title: female body only
826.description: Changes only the body to female. Use with my race undoer (what did I call it again?) target.

827.title: male body only
827.description: Changes only the body to male. Use with my race undoer (what did I call it again?) target.

828.title: male body (fixed nipples)
828.description: Changes only the body to male, with corrected nipples (see bugtracker).

835.title: Motorcycle Jacket
835.description: This motorcycle jacket is made for females. It is armored in front and at the back side. Best fit for females with small cupsize, because for bigger cupsizes the armored parts will be distorted. Delete groups are used. In Blender assign zippers and buttons to a silver-like material. A normalmap is added and is made visible using the leather litsphere.

836.title: Motorcycle Pants
836.description: These motorcycle pants are made for females. It should be combined with the Motorcycle Jacket. Delete groups are used. In Blender assign zippers to a silver-like material. A normalmap is added and is made visible using the leather litsphere. If you want to use Mindfront's biker boots, you have to enlarge the upper part of the boots (see demo picture).

837.title: Martial-Arts Shoes (Kill Bill)
837.description: A pair of shoes used in martial arts derived from my running-shoes with a thinner sole. These shoes are made for the Beatrix Kiddo character (Kill Bill). Delete groups are used. The texture is made manually to make the shoes look like the ones in the movie. A normalmap is supplied and made visible with the leather litsphere.

838.title: Katana (Kill Bill)
838.description: This Hattori Hanzo katana is used by Beatrix Kiddo, the main character of Kill Bill. It is designed on rigid groups. Best way in Blender: duplicate the material and assign the metal parts to the duplicated one. Then make this shader combination glossier (delete fresnel, use fixed value for the mix-node instead and reduce roughness of the glossy shader).

839.title: beatrix kiddo jacket material
839.description: This material should be added to the motorcycle jacket, if your character should look like Beatrix Kiddo in Kill Bill. It uses the normalmap of the standard version.

840.title: beatrix kiddo pants material
840.description: This material should be added to the motorcycle pants, if your character should look like Beatrix Kiddo in Kill Bill. It uses the normalmap of the standard version.

841.title: Patrol Cap
841.description: Tags: Hats, Cap. A simple patrol cap hat with four materials and slightly different diffuse textures and normal maps if you want to use more than one and dont want them to look all the same. The other three materials and textures are in http://www.makehumancommunity.org/materials.html

842.title: Patrol Cap 2
842.description: Version 2 texture and normal map for my "Patrol Cap".

843.title: Patrol Cap 3
843.description: Version 3 texture and normal map for my "Patrol Cap".

844.title: Patrol Cap 4
844.description: Version 4 texture and normal map for my "Patrol Cap".

847.title: Tactical Vest female
847.description:
Tags: Work, Sport, Female. For best fitness I did two version, this is best fitted for a female character.

You may need to adjust the positions of the zipper slider, the shoulder straps and the magazine pockets depending on your character deformations as they use rigid groups, and I leave it to you to deform (sculpt) the pockets so they look more soft and natural as I wanted to keep it as low poly as possible (dont know why as it doesn't matter for my purposes).

The pockets have each three (empty) magazine for an AK47 (i think) and as I did not find any information about their dimension I had to improvise thereof the pockets size but I have seen that some tactical vest pockets are this big.

It is ment to be used with solidify modifier thickness about 2 mm and Fill Rim - Only Rim, or else the pockets and some details wont look as good.

The preview image is rendered in Blender Cycles with the pose "StandingAtEase" by callharvey3d. As I dont yet have made a fitting jacket and trousers I used my "Tank Top 01" and "M Trousers 01" with new textures. On the head is my "Patrol Cap".

848.title: Tactical Vest male
848.description:
Tags: Work, Sport, Male.

For best fitness I did two version, this is best fitted for a male character but the zipper part will get uneven on certain bodies. You may need to adjust the positions of the zipper slider, the shoulder straps and the magazine pockets depending on your character deformations as they use rigid groups, and I leave it to you to deform (sculpt) the pockets so they look more soft and natural as I wanted to keep it as low poly as possible (dont know why as it doesn't matter for my purposes).

The pockets have each three (empty) magazine for an AK47 (i think) and as I did not find any information about their dimension I had to improvise thereof the pockets size but I have seen that some tactical vest pockets are this big.

It is ment to be used with solidify modifier thickness about 2 mm and Fill Rim - Only Rim, or else the pockets and some details wont look as good.

The preview image is rendered in Blender Cycles with the pose "Salute" by callharvey3d. As I dont yet have made a fitting jacket and trousers I used my "Tank Top 01" and "M Trousers 01" with new textures. On the head is my "Patrol Cap".

850.title: Aksel Skin
850.description:
This skin is made by a friend from an original MakeHuman skin, and then I did the normal and specular map from one I have done erlier.
The specular map and normal map have body hair but the skin texture have non but it gives the skin suitable ruffness and you can maybe use the specular map to extract the hair and add on the skin.
In MakeHuman viewport, the normal map looks bad.
Edit 2018-11-04 Removed obsolete links

851.title: M Swimming trunks 03
851.description:
Tags: Male, Swimwear.
I did this for a scene I and a friend working on.
The model is Aksel http://www.makehumancommunity.org/model/character_aksel.html
and his skin is here http://www.makehumancommunity.org/skin/aksel_skin.html

852.title: realistic eyelids
852.description: Makes the eyelid conform more closely to the eyeball, deepening the crease of the upper eyelid.  You may want to use less than 100% of the target on 100% caucasian models, particularly if female. I created this target for the 50% everything startup mesh, results may vary.

854.title: Female Android Basic
854.description:
The basic version of a character from one of my books. I'm using her as an element on a book cover, but perhaps she can do more. 

If you can use her in a game or animation, great, just remember a wink or a nod.

Custom Modifications by Creator (Apologies if I missed any) -- callharvey3d - HarveyStomachMusclesV2, HarveyVCutV1, HarveyNeckDefinitionV1 -- jujube - ear canal, eye_corner_crease -- 
DredNicolson - Breasts  Extra Roundness -- Marco_105 - Body_Shape-05, Waist_bump, Buttocks_THIGH-01, Buttocks_THIGH-03, female_curvy_shape -- Nadow - female-breasts-lift, female-breasts-pushup, female-nipple-right-diameter-incr, female-nipple-left-diameter-incr, female-areola-right-diameter-incr, female-areola-left-diameter-incr -- frankyaye - Vulva_Deep_Low, Vulva_Short, Vulva_Deep_Top, Vulva_Deep_Middle, Vulva_Narrow, Anus_small_length, Anus_small_width

855.title: Short Bodysuit (Female)
855.description: This short bodysuit was made due to an user request. It was intended to create this piece of cloth without the helper-meshes, so the suit behaves quite unnatural in the breast region. The coat of arms is created in a special region of the diffuse texture. I got the rights to use it from the requester, it is an existing irish coat of arms (Wiki: Geoghegan). When you use it in a commercial project, please replace it. Delete groups are used. A normalmap is added, the leather litsphere is used to make it visible in MakeHuman. In Blender connect the color input of the glossy shader to the texture. You can also assign the faces of the zipper to a silver-like material.

856.title: Ghandi_Gown
856.description:
Rather high-poly. Use a subsurf of 2 on top. And the bumpmap as can be seen in the illustration is scaled to a seventh.
The bumptexture derived from a half-sized original tif which is licensed under CC-BY 4.0 ? https://community.renderman.pixar.com/article/114/library-pixar-one-twenty-eight.html?l=r +++ Licensed under CC-BY-NC-SA (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Creative_Commons_license)

857.title: Middle Length Qipao
857.description: I created a modern qipao, even that I used the traditional qipao buttons. For all the users who want to understand the history of the dress, read https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cheongsam ... The dragon pattern for the texture of the piece of cloth is free (https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Datei:Green_Chinese_dragon.PNG), I changed it a bit. A normalmap is added and the litspere is used to make it visible. In Blender change color of the glossy shader to a darker grey or connect it with the image texture. Delete groups are used.

858.title: Mars Suit
858.description: Gender slider set to full male recommended (sorry, sisters). Exporting unsubdivided Mesh recommended. Blender's Subdiv.-Surface-Modifier set to 3, better 4 recommended. The "displacement texture" in fact is an emission map. Look here how to combine normal- and bumpmaps in Cycles: http://www.makehumancommunity.org/forum/viewtopic.php?f=14&t=14595 +++ Edit: new vertex-triplet assigned to the rigid part. No more unwanted deformations. +++ Further useful informations and textures: http://www.makehumancommunity.org/forum/viewtopic.php?f=2&t=14598&p=40240#p40240 +++ Updated mhmat-file for better viewport visibility inside MH. 874.title: Armored Corset (Wonder Woman)
874.description: I tried to create the corset (or corsage) of Wonder Woman using film posters, images of collectible figures etc. So textures and normalmaps are made manually. Delete groups are used, a special rigid group is used at the backside. If you enlarge the cup size too much, the corsage will look funny. To get the same metallic effect, connect the color input of the glossy shader to the output of the texture, reduce roughness to 0.1, delete fresnel and use a fixed value of e.g. 0.7 for the diffuse/glossy mix node. The transparent node is not used. You can also duplicate the material and use a more diffuse mix for the lower leather stripes and the underwear part. The demo picture is created this way.

875.title: Tiara (Wonder Woman)
875.description: The tiara is a piece of headwear, like a crown. To get a similar metal color, connect the color-input of the glossy shader to the texture and use a fixed value for the mix-node e.g. 0.7 instead of the fresnel.

876.title: Bracelet (Wonder Woman)
876.description: This is the bracelet at the upper arm of Wonder Woman. To get a similar metal color, connect the color-input of the glossy shader to the texture and use a fixed value for the mix-node e.g. 0.7 instead of the fresnel.

877.title: Beard Sigmund - wip
877.description: alpha- or beta-version of a beard that follows even the craziest expressions. For now the texture lacks some love. First goal was functionality. This asset was inspired by a very intersting project [http://www.makehumancommunity.org/blogentry/announcing_maketherapist.html]. My thought was that a therapist depends on credibility. Using a face that reminds at the famous analysist Sigmund Freud could help.

880.title: Adult female genitalia remapped
880.description:
I've taken the existing "Adult female genitalia" proxy, and changed its UV map, so that it uses the genitalia textures created for the "Adult female genitalia old" proxy:  you'll find these on the left sides of the texture files for all of the skins whose names end in "female genitals".  The result isn't perfect, because the "female genitalia" and "female genitalia old" proxies have somewhat different topologies (that's why the newer one was created--the older one doesn't look much like the real thing); in addition, both proxies are somewhat asymmetrical, in different ways (the old one more so than the new one).  These two factors result in a certain amount of stretching, but the end result looks pretty good, and it avoids the necessity of having to create textures for all 10 of the "female genitals" skins (and 7 more user-created skins based on them), which is obviously a job nobody has been prepared to do.
EDIT:  Discovered I'd accidentally copied over the UUID from the old proxy, which kept the new proxy from saving correctly.

UPDATE:  Added a tag to the PROXY file.

The one major problem to note  (which also exists when the same skins are used with the "Adult female genitalia old" proxy for which they were created) is that the borders between the remapped section and the rest of the body have sudden color changes in the area behind the vagina.  I've done what I could to minimize the problem, by adjusting the boundaries of both the remapped faces and the adjoining faces on the main texture so that their borders run through colors that match as closely as possible, but you'd have to redo the skins to eliminate the issue entirely, which would to some extent defeat the purpose of the present effort. The same problem exists, to a much smaller extent, along the borders of the front of the remapped area as well (that is, the top of the pubic mound), but it's barely noticeable from most angles.

The THUMB file, BTW, is simply a copy of that used for the other two female genitalia proxies.

881.title: Pink plaid texture for "Low mini-skirt"
881.description: This is a pink plaid texture for "Low mini-skirt"; unlike the original red plaid, this one isn't based on real cloth, but it looks nice enough nonetheless.

882.title: Vambraces (Wonder Woman)
882.description: The right term for the vambraces is "bracelets of submission". But since this jewelry became more and more a part of an armor in the development of Wonder Woman, I use the term vambraces. Textures and normalmaps are made manually. Delete groups are used. To get the same metallic effect, connect the color input of the glossy shader to the output of the texture, reduce roughness to 0.1, delete fresnel and use a fixed value of e.g. 0.7 for the diffuse/glossy mix node. The transparent node is not used. You can also duplicate the material and use a more diffuse mix for the leather stripes. The demo picture is created this way.

883.title: f swimsuit 02
883.description:
I don't know when I started to model this swimsuit. It was supposed to be released about a year ago, but then I discovered several issues including serious modelling mistakes. The big show stoppers got fixed, but I'm still not satisfied with the result. Fixing the remaining issues would require changing the topology which I really don't want to do. So the question was: Release or delete? I finally decided to release it anyway.

Use subsurf 2 and solidify 1mm. Average female used for modelling.

Alternative material available:  http://www.makehumancommunity.org/content/f_swimsuit_02_blue.html.

Update 08/09/2017: For those who want to do their own textures I released two images that might be helpful: http://www.makehumancommunity.org/content/f_swimsuit_02_texture_creation_kit.html.

884.title: f swimsuit 02 blue
884.description: Alternative diffuse texture for the swimsuit.

885.title: Armored Boots (Wonder Woman)
885.description: These boots are modeled using film posters, images of collectible figures etc. So textures and normalmaps are made manually. Delete groups are used, special rigid groups are used for toeboxes and knee-armor. Not every pose will work obviously. To get the same metallic effect, connect the color input of the glossy shader to the output of the texture, reduce roughness to 0.1, delete fresnel and use a fixed value of e.g. 0.7 for the diffuse/glossy mix node. The transparent node is not used. You can also duplicate the material and use a more diffuse mix for the leather straps and the soles. The demo picture is created this way.

886.title: Ponytail01 deep red
886.description:
This material is a deeper red than punkduck's "Ponytail01 red" (http://www.makehumancommunity.org/content/ponytail01_redhead.html), which leans toward strawberry blond.  This one, however, is much simpler--I think I just shifted the color balance in GIMP, and didn't add any of the enhancements found in punkducks material.

EDIT:  attached to the corresponding asset.

887.title: Leather strap (Wonder Woman)
887.description: On this leather strap the "lasso of truth" should be fixed. Textures and normalmaps are made manually. Rigid groups are used on the fasteners at the sides. To get the same metallic effect, connect the color input of the glossy shader to the output of the texture, reduce roughness to 0.1, delete fresnel and use a fixed value of e.g. 0.7 for the diffuse/glossy mix node. The transparent node is not used. You should then duplicate the material and use a more diffuse mix for the leather straps. The demo picture is created this way.

888.title: Lasso (Wonder Woman)
888.description: Wonder Woman's "lasso of truth" belongs to the leather strap, according to all pictures I know, it should be golden. It is created on the same rigid group as this specified part of the leather strap. Textures and normalmaps are made manually. To get the same metallic effect, connect the color input of the glossy shader to the output of the texture, reduce roughness to 0.1, delete fresnel and use a fixed value of e.g. 0.7 for the diffuse/glossy mix node. The transparent node is not used.

889.title: Shield (Wonder Woman, Dawn of Justice)
889.description: This shield Wonder Woman used in the film "Dawn of Justice". It was created from a photo I got from a friend visiting a game-convention, so I had the chance to create a texture, which should be very similar to the real one. Of course a lot of things are painted manually, e.g. most of the letters. I used only one rigid group, but unfortunately the shield deforms when you e.g. change the proportions of your girl. It then becomes oval. To get the same metallic effect, connect the color input of the glossy shader to the output of the texture, reduce roughness to 0.1, delete fresnel and use a fixed value of e.g. 0.7 for the diffuse/glossy mix node. The transparent node is not used. You should then duplicate the material and use a more diffuse mix for the leather straps. The demo picture is created this way. To get the shield of the new Wonder Woman movie, you need this shield and you should also load the different material.

Best export from MH without eyes. No materials yet. Licensed under CC-BY-NC-SA (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Creative_Commons_license)

891.description: This sword Wonder Woman used in the film "Dawn of Justice".  It was created using only one rigid group. To get the same metallic effect, connect the color input of the glossy shader to the output of the texture. The demo picture is created this way.

894.title: Crude T-shirt (female)
894.description:
Seems I forgot to upload this one when I made the crude series. 

The crude series of clothes are intended as starting points for further development. They are mostly low-poly and intended for subdivision (and may therefore look a bit clunky inside MakeHuman). Each piece comes with a plain diffuse texture where the faces have been painted plain white. If you modify or texture paint one of the pieces in this series and want to share, just upload it again here as if you were the original author of it.

Licensed under CC-BY-NC-SA (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Creative_Commons_license)

896.title: F Ninja
896.description:

The hood was difficult to get to deform nicely so I decided to assign it as rigid body, not the best solution as the hood is flattened when rotating the head to look up, I maybe correct that some time. Other parts may be oddly deformed but for the moment the best I could do.

Some texture stretching is noticeable but not too disturbing in my point of view. The face mask is transparent and if you dont want that just remove the usage of alpha on the diffuse texture.

The outfit looks best with at least one level of subsurf and is already solidified.

916.description: Another fashion pose. I used it in the fashion renders. Hands (and arms) did not touch the head or body to allow this pose to be used with other characters, but it will not work with every toon. I did not change the expression to allow a combination of expression and pose. Illustration is made with MakeHuman only.

918.description: For the heel sandals you need different materials, because of the skin. The is the version which fits to the young asian female.

919.description: A fashion pose. I used it in the fashion renders. It could be used for e.g. rejection or fear also. I did not change the expression to allow a combination of expression and pose. Illustration is made with MakeHuman only.

921.title: navel diameter decrease
921.description: If you try to give the navel some depth by using the built-in navel bump slider you'll end up with a crater instead of a belly button. This target decreases the diameter.

922.title: Cycles material for f swimsuit 02
922.description: The swimsuit has three different materials: swimsuit_02_cloth_1, swimsuit_02_cloth_2 and swimsuit_02_clip. You'll see in the illustration where each material belongs to. If you prefer the blue swimsuit you'll need the diffuse texture from http://www.makehumancommunity.org/content/f_swimsuit_02_blue.html. The golden swimsuit (swimsuit_02_cloth_1_gold, swimsuit_02_cloth_2_gold) works differently. It's mostly procedural and uses the textures from http://www.makehumancommunity.org/content/f_swimsuit_02_texture_creation_kit.html as masks. Textures are NOT included in this zip file.

923.title: Skirt (Native American Fashion)
923.description: I created this skirt, which is very similar to an existing one made by an native American designer. Not to get into trouble with copyrights, I used CC0 feathers, scroll and leaves. The glam belt is also made similar to the original. The small spheres may deform unfortunately. You should connect the color input of the glossy shader to the image texture. The buckle in the back may be changed to a silver-like material. For the spheres I changed the white ones to silver and the black ones to a dark glass shader.

924.title: Necklace (Native American Fashion)
924.description: This necklace is similar to a necklace created by a native American designer. In Blender connect the input of the glossy shader to the diffuse texture, duplicate the material and create a diffuse one for the ribbon in the back of the neck. The necklace is NOT made with rigid groups and will deform like the body does.

925.title: Sleeveless Crop Top
925.description: This crop top should fit to most of the dresses. This "initial" version is colored white (like most of the t-shirts you can buy), so it could be simply changed to a new color or pattern. Delete groups are use. You should connect the input of the glossy shader to the output of the image texture.

926.title: Sleeveless Crop Top (Native American Fashion)
926.description: This material contains a slogan presenting another perspective of a fact :-) The text is written with a normal font, so there should be no copyright problems. Normally this text is printed on t-shirts and not on crop tops. This material uses the normal map of the standard material.

927.description: First attempt to create makehuman cloths I choosed something simple: A white,transparent pantyhose.

928.title: Optical Glasses

929.title: Running race
929.description: This is a running pose that I made as an alternative to the Run01 pose supplied with MakeHuman 1.1.0.

930.description: The french lingerie (suspender-belt, also called garter belt) is part of a set containing briefs, stockings, suspender-belt and bra. A black material is added also.

931.title: french lingerie (suspender-belt, black material)
931.description: This material should be used for the suspender-belt of the french lingerie. It uses the normal map of the white material in the parent directory.

932.title: french lingerie (stockings)
932.description: The french lingerie (stockings) is part of a set containing briefs, stockings, suspender-belt and bra. A black material is also available. In Blender reduce glossiness and connect input of the glossy shader to the texture. No delete groups are used, so skin may peek through in certain poses.

933.title: french lingerie (stockings, black material)
933.description: Black material for the stockings of the french lingerie.

934.title: Eyes with alternative topology
934.description: These eyes use a single mesh with a cornea.  If you set the cornea (bump over the iris) material to glass you will get a much closer model of the eye than the default, and avoid things like dark corners in the eye and reflections off the iris.  The glass need only be the Cycles Glass shader with default settings "wired" directly to the material output node.

a rework of harvey midtoned female, i removed moles on the back of left arm and some other stuff, adjusted the color to get that sexy creamy skin i wanted and added some lipstick. workes best with the adult female genitalia remapped.


big thx to Callharvey3D for sharing the original and all the other great stuff you publish

937.title: Rig for Makehuman 1.0.2 for Unity 2017 and Lower.
937.description:
If you have old humanoids in Makehuman 1.0.2, here is the solution.
JSON file for Rigging in Makehuman 1.0.2 for Unity 2017 and Lower.
Put the unity.json and unity thumb in:
C:\(Where you have installed)\data\rigs.
Example: C:\Program Files (x86)\Makehuman-1.0.2\data\rigs
Don't worry about T-Pose, it will adapt perfect for animations.

938.title: classic tutu opaque
938.description:
This is an opaque version of the original material--I just set the alpha in the original diffuse texture to 1.0 throughout.

EDIT:   I've just corrected the spelling of the name.

939.description: This texture was baked using wolgade's original instructions.  It won't look as good in Blender as doing things the hard way, but it allows you to see in Makehuman what the ring will look like.

940.title: diamond earring left baked
940.description: This texture was baked using wolgade's original instructions.  It won't look as good in Blender as doing things the hard way, but it allows you to see in Makehuman what the ring will look like.  The PNG file for the left and right earrings is identical.

941.title: diamond earring right baked
941.description: This texture was baked using wolgade's original instructions.  It won't look as good in Blender as doing things the hard way, but it allows you to see in Makehuman what the ring will look like.  The PNG file for the left and right earrings is identical.

942.title: Steampunk/Goth Jacket corrected
942.description: This MHMAT file corrects a few problems with the original:  the diffuse color is set to neutral, the shininess is turned down, and I removed backface culling so that the inside of the collar doesn't disappear.  It's probably best just to substitute this file for the original (it uses the same texture files).

943.title: BSoM Astronaut Belt
943.description:
"Building Site on Mars" Astronaut
Male (version 1, to be updated)

In summer I resurrected my first blender video project "Building Site on Mars" (see https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=36m_97hCReg) for "next generation".
In this context I ported the austronaut to makehuman to create more than one individuum.

Feel free to enhance this figure or to create your own astronaut.

Therefore the blender file, including Gimp XCF for textures is uploaded at:
http://www.makehumancommunity.org/content/bsom_astronaut_blender_project_including_cycles_materials.html
There are special texture images for cycles (transparent) marked as "_cycles".
The cloths are created for standard male.
Unfortunally other characters have deformations basing on the nature of exporting special groups (see below).
So if someone has a solution for this problem, please comment it...

There are a few todos on this item, especially details and textures.
I hope to handle this the next weeks...
To get updated...

Belt: Problem of deformation when changing the character - see readme in zip.

944.title: BSoM Astronaut Blender Project including Cycles Materials.
944.description:
"Building Site on Mars" Astronaut
Male (version 1, to be updated)

In summer I resurrected my first blender project "Building Site on Mars" (see https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=36m_97hCReg) for "next generation".
In this context I ported the austronaut to makehuman to create more than one individuum.
Feel free to enhance this figure or to create your own astronaut.

Zip File, including Gimp XCF for textures.

There are special texture images for cycles (transparent) marked as "_cycles".

The cloths are created for standard male.
Unfortunally other characters have deformations basing on the nature of exporting special groups (see below).
So if someone has a solution for this problem, please comment it...

ATTENTION! In the blender file there are more than one materials which must be removed before creating cloths.
So before exporting your cloth don't forget to delete the cycles materials. - Materials for Cloth export begin with "blender_".
The best way is to save as temporary blender file before creating, to prevent lost of cycles materials.

After import to the new project it's possible to append the materials. - It's just a little work to reassign the materials to your new character.
The best way will be the selection in the UV Map.

It's important to reconfigure the paths for textures in the blender file, particulary because we are working with linux.

Have fun to use this project for creation of your own Astronauts or creating your own scenes/videos.
Attribution is appreciated. ;)

954.title: Denim Jacket
954.description: This jacket should fit to the tight jeans, short jeans, sleeveless crop top, tube top and spaghetti strap tank top nerely without changing topology. Best way to use the material in Blender: duplicate it and use a less glossy version for the fabric (e.g. connect input color of glossy shader to output of diffuse texture, you can also delete the fresnel and use a fixed value instead), use the glossy version for the buttons (set roughness of glossy shader to a low value). 982.title: Adult Female Genitalia (old) HEALED
982.description:
The original proxy "Adult Female Genitalia (old)" does not interact well with morph targets and animations, because the algorithm used to generate the barycentric coordinates of each new point relied too heavily on orthogonal projection. This is what causes the median vertices (in the YZ plane) to have "random" displacements along X when morphed or animated (the correct projection of those vertices lies on an edge in the YZ plane, rather than on any of the adjacent faces). The perineum was messed up a lot too, because it is the area that deforms the most for even the most basic morphs. Orthogonal projection onto alternative triangulations of non-planar quads also caused some discontinuities in the weight map.

I kept the original mesh and topology but regenerated the proxy from scratch, with a consistent projection algorithm (straight line towards root point, and only one triangulation for each quad), using the "Fight4" pose as a benchmark. The perineum area still required some tweaking, because the area weighted to the spine (rather than the hips or legs) is so narrow for the base morph. I also tweaked a few vertices here and there to get a smoother look, and I made sure the proxy data was symmetrical. The minor tweaks are not reflected in the OBJ file, which is exactly the same as the original: so, exact same topology and exact same UVs (which will work as intended with all the materials/skins named "... female[|2] genitals").

The result is in no way perfect, but it can be a decent reference for further improvements. The perineum is one problem (still not smooth enough, depending on the morph and animation). The other problem is the transition from the labia major to the inside of the legs (clearly visible with the "Benchmark" pose, but could look messed-up even for some actually useful poses). To resolve this, one can tweak the projection rules, or one can widen the crotch area of the base mesh (through an appropriate morph), generate the proxy using this custom base, and then apply the reverse morph when modeling, to recover the original aspect. One can also redesign the morphology and add more vertices in the areas that deform the most.

The OBJ file will be updated when and if those further improvements occur. In the meantime, enjoy.

1026.title: Adult Female Genitalia (new) HEALED
1026.description: Like the "old" female genitalia proxy, the newer one (named simply "Adult Female Genitalia") did not deform properly when morphed or animated. I regenerated the proxy with a simple projection along Y, and it works OK now. The UVs stay close to those of the original OBJ, in that they do not map to the detailed female genitalia texture (which works best with the "old" proxy). Instead I used the male genital regions that are present on all of the base textures. The result is a bit toon-like, but I think it fits in well with the coarse detail of the mesh itself. If you prefer the "remapped" UVs by MTKnife, you can use that OBJ instead, since it's the exact same topology (be sure to remove the binary *.npz file after you swap the *.obj, so that MakeHuman knows to regenerate the topology with the new UVs). Future versions may include remodeling/retexturing, but really it's the messed-up vertex weights that I felt like fixing. P.S. I also cleaned up a few vertices in the neck area that were shifted for no apparent reason, and made sure the proxy was entirely symmetric (except maybe for the UVs).

1148.title: Ice Skates (Figure Skates)
1148.description: These ice skates can be combined with the ballet tights and leotard or other appropriate clothes. The blades and the sole (in reality using several leather and cork layers) are created on rigid groups, because they should not deform. Delete groups are used.  In Blender: select all vertices of the blades (own geometry) and assign them to a glossy copy of the original material. To get the same metallic effect, connect the color input of the glossy shader to the output of the texture, reduce roughness to 0.1, delete fresnel and use a fixed value of e.g. 0.7 for the diffuse/glossy mix node. The transparent node is not used. The demo picture is created this way. A normalmap is also added.

1234.title: F Dress 05
1234.description:
Tags: Female, Elegant.

This dress is quite hard to get to deform nicely especially the sleeves, Blender's modifier "Surface Deform" and "Corrective Smooth" is good help. The base dress is designed by my friend Bellatrix and wanted to share it with MakeHuman community.

I am not satisfied with the normal map skirt folds but lesser real folds make it easier to adjust.

In Blender use the Solidify modifier with thickness about 1,5mm, fill rim and only rim to give the fabric some thickness.

I use the slot for displacement for the metal mask texture.

The preview image is rendered in Blender Cycles and I used proportional edit, sculpt, "Surface Deform" and "Corrective Smooth" modifier to adjust the dress to fit the character and pose. (The fabric looks like it is made of metal but my intention was silk and of some reason appear more pink than intended.)

The Blender 2.79 material I use can be downloaded here: http://www.makehumancommunity.org/content/f_dress_05_blender_cycles.html

1236.description:
Tags: Female, Elegant.

This dress is my own design as I was in making a dress mood. Not so practical in ordinary life but good to have in the closet till New Years Eve.

I use the slot for displacement for the metal mask texture.

It does not need any subdivision as I accidentally applied one level.
In Blender use the Solidify modifier with thickness about 2mm, fill rim and only rim to give the fabric some thickness.

The preview image is rendered in Blender Cycles and I used proportional edit and sculpt to adjust the dress to fit the character and pose.

The Blender 2.79 material I use can be downloaded here: http://www.makehumancommunity.org/content/f_dress_06_blender_cycles.html

In the end you should decrease the roughness of the glossy shader. That's the way the example picture was done. Be aware that parts will deform when changing the geometry or posing the character. 1323.title: Animeeple_makehuman
1323.description:
This rig/skeleton is the same rig than the default MH rig  but bones are renamed in order to make the importation into Animeeple automatic.

Animeeple (0.418)  is a free and very easy soft to use to make human animations , camera motion , overlap animations , loops, etc ... make a basic render in video, and/or export the result. 


Import/Export : dae , fbx (just import) , bvh (just animations) , xml  


Use :  export your MH model in T-pose with this rig (fbx is good)  , and while import it in Animeeple,  just click on "Drop on floor" and "Reset" button to make it fit.   Also, you might have to check if all the textures are ok and configure things such opacity, specular .. etc  


Animeeple is no longer developped but i put a copy of the latest version (0.4.18) -------------------------------------- http://www.filedropper.com/animeeple   -------------------------------------- -------------------------------------- -------------------------------------- -------------------------------------- -------------------------------------- -------------------------------------- --------------------------------------  If the model you are working on is already made with the default MH skeleton ; look down in the comments; i copy-pasted the Blender script that will rename automaticaly your bones to make it animeeple-compatible.

1483.title: one piece bikini01
1483.description: This is a one piece bikini. It is colored white and there is a node setup supplied, so that you can recolor it (e.g. like in "Baywatch"). There is also advice how to use the shrinkwrap modifier to make it skin-tight. A normal-map is also supplied. Delete-groups are used. Be aware to switch them off, when you will work with transparency. There are also two methods to simulate a wet swimsuit, one is simply to reduce roughness of the glossy node. There is also a second texture added, where transparency is used except where the seams and crotch-area are. This is more "sexy". Be aware that for a dark color you need less(!) transparency to make the skin visible. But decide yourself, which way you like ...

1484.title: one piece bikini01 (semi-transparent)
1484.description: This is a special material for the one piece bikini. For the node setup, see the original asset. The normal-map is also used. Be aware that you must switch the delete-groups off. This is a method to simulate a wet swimsuit. Be aware that for a dark color you need less(!) transparency to make the skin visible. The seams and the crotch-area are not transparent. This asset is rather explicit. If you want a wet swimsuit without the skin visible, use the original texture and reduce roughness of the glossy node.

1623.title: Diamond Ring 1.5 Carat - Right
1623.description:
This diamond ring is based on wolgade's diamond ring.
http://www.makehumancommunity.org/clothes/diamond_ring_01.html
It has a bigger diamond, and there are versions of it for both the left and right hands -- this one is for the right. 
I have included a UV texture, but like most jewelry assets, this ring doesn't work "out of the box."  It really needs two procedural materials, and the faces of the diamond should be shaded flat, while the ring should be shaded smooth. 
I have uploaded a .blend with diamond and gold materials for Blender Internal.
http://www.makehumancommunity.org/content/diamond_and_gold_materials_for_blender_internal.html
And for those who do Cycles, wolgade's Cycles gold and diamond tutorial is here:
http://www.makehumancommunity.org/forum/viewtopic.php?f=4&t=13910

1703.title: F Dress 11
1703.description: Bellatrix made this fabric print and design, which I textured and MakeHumanized. From now, if necessary, I will start making also displacement maps for better visualization of larger folds without the need of deliver a high topology mesh. The displacement map is suited for 2x subsurf and in scale 1:1 displacement strength 0.1 . In Blender use the Solidify modifier with thickness about 2.5 mm, fill rim and only rim to give the fabric some thickness, and if you use displacement modifier, solidify modifier must be placed after to avoid distortions of the skirt rim. This time I use the "Optional bump texture" slot for the metal mask texture. The preview image is rendered in Blender Cycles and I used proportional edit and sculpt to adjust the dress to fit the character and pose.

1711.title: NSMakeHumanBipedController Alpha 0.1

1. Create A Human
2. Set Skeleton to "Unity with Breast and Butts"
3.Export as FBX
4. Import in 3DS MAX (2018 Tested)
5. Create a Biped and load the Figure in "Biped-Figure-Mode"
6. Set Biped in the Correct Position
7. Run Script

1761.title: Bento Alpha 1
1761.description: First try of a Bento skeleton, some weights are still not 100%. Most weights are generated from the default skeleton. In some parts it is identical to the OpenSim skeleton, but I changed the joints according to the real skeleton. I supported all bones "inside" the basic mesh. So no wings, no tail, no hind legs in this skeleton. Also the 4 special bones folded in spine region are not added in this version. For Sim-World: use Bento-T-Pose for export from MakeHuman to Blender via mhx2 (size must be meter), import in Blender using default mode and export as Collada dae using SL/OpenSim activated. For poses use e.g. Avastar. This is necessary because Sims have different rotation planes. This Bento skeleton also works for normal Blender characters. Some parts are better than in default-skeleton (like eyebrows in my opinion), some are not so good (shoulders). When you prefer working in Blender directly, don't use Bento-T-Pose, use normal A-Pose (because of the fingers).

1765.title: Ballet Costume
1765.description:
Tags: male, ballet, work.
A ballet costume designed by Bellatrix.

Texture made for 1x subsurf. On some characters the shirt may leak through the vest. Only using MakeClothes automatic vertex group binding.

In Blender use the solidify modifier, 2.5 mm thickness and "Fill Rim" and "Only Rim" to give the fabric and lacing some thickness.

The displacement texture is made for subsurf level 2 (or more) to give the folds some more shapes. The Displacement Modifier as for Blender 2.79 should be set to "Midlevel 0.502" "Strength 0.1". (as Midlevel 0.5 seems not to be neutral level.)

The preview image is rendered in Blender Cycles after some proportional editing and sculpting to better fit the character and pose.

1835.title: heels angle
1835.description:
This target should be used for high-heeled shoes, but only for the shoes which are created for targets! So not for heel poses with bones and also not for shoes where the vertices of the feet were deleted by special vertex-groups, e.g. most boots in MakeHuman. This target does not make much sense, when no high-heeled shoes are used (or may also create odd effects). Some of the heel targets must be used in combination to fit the shoes. This is a work-around, because a special helper is not yet available. Put this target into a subfolder of your "custom" folder for better usage e.g. "heels", especially because you may need different heel targets. This target creates the foot angle. 

Examples:
http://www.makehumancommunity.org/forum/download/file.php?id=7225&mode=view

from article:
http://www.makehumancommunity.org/forum/viewtopic.php?f=14&t=17208

1961.title: Pleated miniskirt
1961.description:
I really wanted to do pleats by creating a mesh in the right shape, rather than using normals....It took me close to two years off and on to figure out how to do that.  The pleats are in fact folded just like real knife pleats (a good guide for making the real thing is https://www.carbonchic.com.au/2014/11/diy-knife-pleated-skirt/), or rather one pleat was folded and then repeated along a bezier curve made from an edge loop in the skirt helper (this introduced some distortions in size, but they're not horrible).  The mesh was designed with quads, then transformed to tris (using "poke faces") before being exported as clothes, in order to deal with the non-planar faces necessarily created by the folding.  The peculiar format of the UV map is also due to folding the mesh like real pleats:  to get pixels to end up in the right places, the texture needs to be a long strip, just like a real pleated skirt is made from a long strip of fabric.  Finally, note that if you want to do a cloth simulation on the skirt, you'll need to do some pinning, as the pleats aren't actually attached to the waistband. 

Credits:  In the included material, the plaid texture comes from heartlessinu at DeviantArt (https://www.deviantart.com/heartlessinu/art/Red-plaid-215324313), while the zipper is from fuzzimo (http://www.fuzzimo.com/free-hi-res-zipper-textures-pictures/).

UPDATE:  Straightened some of the geometry in the waistband, and fixed a few problems that show up on specific models.

1962.title: Chiton Doric 01 female
1962.description:
Tags: Female, Casual. An ancient greece doric chiton for female characters. The fibulas may be displaced and loose their shape on some characters.

This textures also works on the male version as sharing same UV-layout.

For practical reasons I decided to make a separate alpha texture instead of using the png alpha channel, uploaded in the BUMP-slot. This also makes it possible to save as jpeg.

The preview image is rendered in Blender Cycles using 2x subsurf, displace modifier and a material using the separate alpha texture. Then some manual adjustments to better fit the character and pose.

1964.title: Mind Eyebrows 01
1964.description:
Mesh (high poly) eyebrows as an alternative to (low poly) textured. Instead of using Blender particle eyebrows I decided to make them as mesh to be reusable through MakeHuman. Each hair is non-manifold triangular and goes about 1 mm into the head to avoid visible gaps when posing.

Same eyebrows can look awful on some characters and better on other.

No texture is needed but they are UV-unwrapped with the roots at the bottom. If you want them darker at the roots and lighter at the tips you can make a BW gradient texture as color mix factor. 

The preview render is on a default neutral character, using subsurf x1 and a simple cycles material.

2143.title: Slender 18 year old Caucasian male
2143.description:
This is the best I could do with the knowledge I have and the available tools. Model is a skinny nude Caucasian with long hair, bright blue eyes, custom skin, fingernails, toenails, eyebrows, default skeleton, and defualt penis length. His muscle is maximum, and weight is minimum. He uses the following custom targets maxed to 100:

-Armpit
-Elvs male nipple 1
-Harvey neck definition 1
-Harvey stomach muscles*
-Harvey v cut v 1
-Septim sharp

*Harvey's stomach muscles and Elvs maleproxy1 don't work well together for some reason. Elvs maleproxy1 is the best choice for making a male character, but it does something to Harvey's stomach muscles and makes them less defined. I tried to correct this, but I don't know how. Perhaps someone with some skill can improve on my design and make the muscles more defined. The body seems perfect in most other areas.

Custom hair, genitals, skin, and nipples by Elv. No custom parts of the character are mine, I just used them. This character can be used as a base to be improved upon.

2551.title: Shelly Blake
2551.description:
Shelly Blake is a bronze tanned Caucasian female aged 29 years from New York City. She is tall and curvy with long ginger hair. She is a hippy chick, somewhat on the trashy side. She enjoys drinking wine and smoking weed. She is also a computer programmer and designer of artificial human skins (robots) and appointments. Shelly was modeled from the default base using the controls native to MakeHuman. She was tuned to have proportional fat and medium muscle. Her face has full features and a proper double chin. She is free to use for non commercial projects. Licenses apply to the linked assets. To generate her in MakeHuman as illustrated, you will need the following assets to be installed in your data directory:

- Long01 Hair included with MakeHuman -

- Long01 Hair Ginger material: http://www.makehumancommunity.org/content/long_01_ginger.html -

- Light skin female bronze: http://www.makehumancommunity.org/skin/light_skin_female_bronze.html -

- Eyes: High poly included with MakeHuman, cannot find link to green texture -

2554.title: Low poly with mouth interior
2554.description:
I wanted a low poly proxy with a mouth interior because I wanted to animate the mouth from inside a game engine (Unity) which has backface culling turned on by default, so I was getting this annoying hole out the back of their head whenever I opened their mouth.

This mesh is "Male1591" from vanilla MakeHuman 1.2.0 Beta1, removed the tongue (why did it have a built-in tongue anyway?) and added a mouth interior. I made some slight adjustments to the lips to get it to export from MakeClothes2 properly.

This is my first contribution to the MakeHuman community and I'm excited to have this opportunity! I love open source software and I intend to continue contributing whenever I have something of value to share.

2711.title: Long 01 Bronze
2711.description: A beautiful shiny bronze color for the Long 01 hair included with MakeHuman. All elements of this material, other than the color, are part of the default file set for Long01 hair included with MakeHuman. This material is a simple MAT file to change the actual hair color. It is one of many custom shades created by Ricardo2020 for this default hairstyle. To incorporate this hair into your installation, place the thumb and mat files into the materials folder within the Hair/Long01 folder inside the data folder for v1 of MakeHuman. To use the file, load a model and go to the geometries>hair tab and select Long01 in the styles thumbnails on the right. Then, go to the Materials tab and look for Long01 on the left. Select it and go to Bronze material thumbnail on the right. Continue modeling. The color is now assigned and you can work on other aspects of your project. To make the change permanent for the model, simply save the model.

2712.title: Juicy Lucy
2712.description:
Lucy MacIntire is a petite and chubby young woman about 21 years of age. She is of Irish decent, from Fredricksburg in Newfoundland, Canada. Lucy is a curve model working for the fashion magazine circuit as a freelance artist. She is very easy going and fun loving, with a weakness for Stoli vodka and Kalua. She is a musician who enjoys playing her folk guitar while singing at coffee houses and small cafe settings. She is single and has no intentions of finding a boyfriend any time soon, but she is always interested in playing around with the right fellow now and then.

Lucy was modelled in MakeHuman using a set of custom control targets. These can be downloaded and installed from the Assets/Targets page on this website. These files go into the MakeHuman/V1/Data/Custom folder. They will appear in the Modeling/Custom tab inside Makehuman once installed. When loaded in the program, Lucy will be nude. Dress her as you wish, but know that she likes loose fitting attire. If Hide Faces Under Clothing is selected in Geometries tab, some meshes will render torn if the cloth does not follow the base mesh topography and custom tageting.

To learn more about Lucy's asset requirements and how to set her up as shown, please visit her forum page at http://www.makehumancommunity.org/forum/viewtopic.php?f=4&t=18973

2822.title: UE4 A-Pose for generic male
2822.description: Unreal Engine SK_Mannequin compatible A-pose for generic male. NOTE: This pose is provided in good faith as is and I do not have time to help you rig your own characters. This pose is a near drop in fit for the Unreal mannequin using a generic male with standard proportions and 187.5 cm height. Bone rotations were overlaid and painstakingly matched to the standard reference skeleton. The results work with Blender using the MHX2 exchange format. See the attached reference image. The stick figure is the Makehuman skeleton used in this pose overlaid on the UE4 skeleton. Minor adjustments to the mannequin skeleton (head, neck, wrist, fingers, hips, feet) are recommended before rigging to get a perfect fit and accurate automatic weights.

Bone rotations were overlaid and painstakingly matched to the standard reference skeleton. The results work with Blender using the MHX2 exchange format. See the attached reference image. The stick figure is the Makehuman skeleton used in this pose overlaid on the UE4 skeleton. Minor adjustments to the mannequin skeleton (head, neck, wrist, fingers, hips, feet) are recommended before rigging to get a perfect fit and accurate automatic weights.

2827.title: Caldonia Watson
2827.description:
Caldonia Watson is a large lady in her early thirties who lives on Mars in the city of Mount Olympus. In the year 2147, a colony has been established for the purpose of terraforming the planet and building a gateway to the outer solar system. Caldonia is a diplomat working with the Martian Government to create an independent society free of the spoils of Earth. She advocates for a free culture where honest folks get out what they put in and nobody gets a free pass without hard work..

Caldonia has a bubbly, outgoing personality and she laughs a lot. Her hair is long and her body is soft, but underneath the ample curves, she is a strong woman who should not be trifled with casually. She is very forgiving but her memory is long and she forgets nothing. It is hard to fool her about anything since she is a keen observer who listens first and talks later with a tiny soft voice.

The SSBBW model is made using many custom targets. Caldonia will load nude in Make Human. Due to her large size, most of the clothing assets will not fit. To use certain assets, it might be prudent to export her and the clothing in question into blender and modify the meshes to get them to fit. There are standard items which require no modification, however, so simply try out some items to see what happens.

2883.title: Young African Female with Genitals *Use Instructions*
2883.description:
[What is this] 
My edit of the Young African Female with Genitals diffuse. All this does is position and scale part of the genital (lower lady bits) texture that is provided by wolgade. I didn't make any changes to the breasts. It could be way better, so feel free to download wolgade's genital skin and do a better job than this. In fact, I would greatly appreciate it if you choose to upload it here! I need quality textures for game development purposes.

[How to use/Guide]
This guide is written for windows 10 users. Parts of the guide will be relevant on other operating systems as well.

[1] Click the link on the mhmat file. It will probably open up a text file in your web browser. Right click anywhere on the page and select "Save as" to save it to your pc. MAKE SURE THE FILE EXTENSION IS "MHMAT" AND NOT MHMAT.TXT!

[2] Click on the thumb link and right click to save just as before. File extension will be "thumb".

[3] Click on the picture under "Optional diffuse texture" and right click to save as you did before.

[4] Find the mhmat and thumb files you downloaded earlier. Copy them. On your PC, navigate to your documents folder. Inside, there should be a folder "makehuman". Click on it and go to v1py3 -> data -> skins. Create a folder and name it "young_african_female_genitals" inside the skins folder. Go into the folder you just created and paste your mhmat and thumb files there. 

[5] Find the optional diffuse file you downloaded earlier. Copy it. Navigate back to the data folder and navigate inside "textures". Paste the diffuse texture inside here.

[6] While inside the "textures" folder, right click the box that contains text that looks like "Documents > makehuman > v1py3 > data > textures" and select "copy address as text".

[7] Find the mhmat file inside the "young_african_female_genitals" folder you created earlier. Open it with a text editor (such as Notepad or Notepad++, Google opening files with Notepad if you don't know how). On line 27 of the text in the editor, you should see 
"diffuseTexture <path to folder>\young_darkskinned_female_genitals_diffuse.png". Delete "<path to folder>" and paste the address you copied earlier there instead. Save.

[8] Go into MakeHuman. Click on materials at the top, and on the left make sure "skin" is selected. On the right, you should see a bunch of skins you can select. The genital skin should be in the list. For me, it's directly underneath the default "Young african female" skin.

[Warnings] Do not rename the files unless you know what you are doing. Also, make sure your file extensions are the ones I mentioned in the guide. If you can't see file extensions, Google how to make them visible. It's okay to delete the ".txt" off the mhmat file. If you get a prompt after doing so, click "Yes".

[Final Word] If you have any problems, let me know. This guide is pretty bad, but I struggled with figuring out how to use other people's uploaded skins for AGES. The guides that exist leave too much out. It's here as SOMETHING at least.

3038.title: Elvs Downfaced Breast 1
3038.description:
Part of a series of targets with a focus on large female bodies. These should work together to create a fuller figured female model in makehuman.
They also should work with the new hormonal and primitive body shapes available in makehuman now. Also most are useful individually to alter
one specific area of the body. Some targets are quite strong, and therefore a gentle hand may be needed for desired results, however this allows
them to work with ssbw bodies also. When mixing the targets together, an especially delicate touch is needed to achieve a realistic shape. That being said
at times, targets do not play nicely with certain clothing items or stock sliders etc.
As time allows I will upload as many of these finished targets as possible, firstly female then male. Ty to Ricardo and the makehuman Devs, for the help
and inspiration on the process in this ongoing project. These targets, for this project,are all CC0.

3185.title: ssbbw_256
3185.description: Super Size Big Beautiful Woman number 256, a full body target designed to be applied to the default base in MakeHuman Community v1.2.x, compatibility has not been tested on earlier versions, so comment below if problems crop up during use. To use this file, right click and download the item to your data/custom/targets folder inside the home directory for MakeHuman. This will vary with different operating systems, but they all seem to have a user area for this kind of thing. After putting the file in its proper place, launch MakeHuman and click the custom tab under modeling. Look for the file in the sliders on the left. Move the slider all the way to the right to apply the target with the strength it is designed to run at. Dial it to the left to create a thinner more skinny version of the model. Height is 5'4". Weight is 269 lbs. Age is 30's. Race is a mix of African and Caucasian. Fat to muscle ratio favors fat. Slow endocrine, mostly thyroid. Morbidly obese but still active. Average resistance to disease. Average endurance non aerobic. High intellect and mild mannered. Native of Knox County, Tennessee.

3220.title: Black Kameri Fur
3220.description:
The Kameri are a humaonid species with black and white striped fur, which jokingly call themselves two-legged zebra.
Usually black dominates the coat pattern and the stripes are white. Very rarely there is a variant in which white dominates as the basic color.
This is the usual black dominated coat.

Important: Kameri are hermaphrodite and always appear in female appearance. To reproduce, a Kameri can turn her vagina inside out and reshape it into a penis to fertilize her mate. So please don't anyone come up with the idea of giving birth to male Kameri. They do not exist.

There's nothing magical about the scene, but it's a good start when experimenting with characters. Light setup is configured for both cycles and eevee.

3227.title: SSBBW 453
3227.description: Super Size Big Beautiful Woman number 453, a full body target for creating a middle age petite woman of size, designed to be applied to the default base in MakeHuman Community v1.2.x, compatibility has not been tested on earlier versions, so comment below if problems crop up during use. To use this file, right click and download the item to your data/custom/targets folder inside the home directory for MakeHuman. This will vary with different operating systems, but they all seem to have a user area for this kind of thing. After putting the file in its proper place, launch MakeHuman and click the custom tab under modeling. Look for the file in the sliders on the left. Move the slider all the way to the right to apply the target with the strength it is designed to run at. Dial it to the left to create a thinner more skinny version of the model. Height is 5'3". Weight is 260 lbs. Age is 40. Race is Caucasian. Fat to muscle ratio favors fat. Slow endocrine, mostly thyroid. Morbidly obese but active. Average resistance to disease. Average endurance. High intellect and very friendly. She is from a time in the future (22nd century) and is a native of Vallus Mar, Mars.

3240.title: Improved normalmap shader
3240.description:
This is an improved version of the built in "normalmap" shader which also takes the roughness map into consideration. Becuase of a limitation in makehuman, it cannot access the "roughnessmapTexture" keyword in the .mhmat file, so a work-around is necessary. Here's how to use it:

1) Put the two files into C:\Users\username\Documents\makehuman\v1py3\data\shaders\glsl\ or wherever your data folder is.
2) Find an .mhmat file that a "roughnessmapTexture" specified
3) Copy that line (but keep the original) and change the copy to "specularmapTexture blablabla.jpg"
4) Make sure that the material has this line: shader shaders/glsl/normalmap2

Tip: The specularmapTexture (grayscale) works like this: Dark means "shiny" like glass, bright means "diffuse" like cloth.
